disableSwipeToOpen.description: If true, swiping sideways when the Drawer is closed will not open it.

docked.description:
If true, the Drawer will be docked. In this state, the overlay won't show and clicking on a
menu item will not close the Drawer.

open.description:
If true, the Drawer is opened. Whether true or false, ensures that the drawer is a controlled
component.

openSecondary.description: If true, the Drawer is positioned to open from the opposite side.

swipeAreaWidth.description:
The width of the left most (or right most) area in pixels where the Drawer can be swiped
open from. Setting this to null spans that area to the entire page (CAUTION! Setting this
property to null might cause issues with sliders and swipeable Tabs: use at your own risk).

width.description:
The width of the Drawer in pixels or percentage in string format ex. 50% to fill half of the
window or 100% and so on. Defaults to using the values from theme.

children.description:
This is what will be displayed inside the button.
If a label is specified, the text within the label prop will
be displayed. Otherwise, the component will expect children
which will then be displayed. (In our example,
we are nesting an `<input type="file" />` and a `span`
that acts as our label to be displayed.) This only
applies to flat and raised buttons.

style.description: Override the inline-styles of the root element.

autoGenerateNestedIndicator.description:
If true, generate a nested-list-indicator icon when nested list items are detected.
Note that an indicator will not be created if a rightIcon or rightIconButton has been
provided to the element.

containerElement.description:
The element to use as the container for the ListItem. Either a string to use a DOM element
or a ReactElement. This is useful for wrapping the ListItem in a custom Link component.
If a ReactElement is given, ensure that it passes all of its given props through to the
underlying DOM element and renders its children prop for proper integration.

disabledKeyboardFocus.description: If true, the element will not be able to be focused by the keyboard.

disabled.description:
If true, the element will not be clickable and will not display hover effects.
This is automatically disabled if either leftCheckbox or rightToggle is set.

fireEvent.description: Dash-assigned callback that gets fired when the input changes.

initiallyOpen.description: If true, the nested ListItems are initially displayed.

innerDivStyle.description: Override the inline-styles of the inner div element.

insetChildren.description:
If true, the children will be indented by 72px. This is useful if there is no left
avatar or left icon.

isKeyboardFocused.description:
Use to control if the list item should render as keyboard focused. If undefined (default),
this will be automatically managed. If provided, it will change the component's style.
Note that this will not change the actual focus - and should only be used when you want to
simulate keyboard focus (eg. in a rich text input autocomplete).

leftAvatar.description: This is the Avatar element to be displayed on the left side.

leftCheckbox.description: This is the Checkbox element to be displayed on the left side.

leftIcon.description: This is the SvgIcon or FontIcon to be displayed on the left side.

nestedItems.description: An array of ListItems to nest underneath the current ListItem.

nestedListStyle.description: Override the inline-styles of the nested items' NestedList.

open.description: Control toggle state of nested list.

primaryText.description:
This is the block element that contains the primary text. If a string is passed in,
a div tag will be rendered.

primaryTogglesNestedList.description: If true, clicking or tapping the primary text of the ListItem toggles the nested list.

rightAvatar.description: This is the Avatar element to be displayed on the right side.

rightIcon.description: This is the SvgIcon or FontIcon to be displayed on the right side.

rightIconButton.description:
This is the IconButton to be displayed on the right side. Hovering over this button will
remove the ListItem hover. Also, clicking on this button will not trigger a ripple on the
ListItem; the event will be stopped and prevented from bubbling up to cause a ListItem click.

rightToggle.description: This is the Toggle element to display on the right side.

secondaryText.description:
This is the block element that contains the secondary text. If a string is passed in,
a div tag will be rendered.

secondaryTextLines.description: Can be 1 or 2. This is the number of secondary text lines before ellipsis will show.
